Friends,

A quick update: I've had to give up on the idea of creating a nonprofit
around the personal data locker concept, because it was too difficult to
raise money. I'm now working on raising the world's first venture fund to
accelerate the development of the open Metaverse
<https://medium.com/the-metaverse/why-the-metaverse-will-be-huge-f904a3a3d2a?sk=cf57e29a7f9b0b29f92dc9f279ec0f4c>.
I have a good fundraising partner, Arnold Yanovich. I have a few good
advisors. Initial feedback is that we are in a very good position to raise
a fund - people we've spoken to all say they are interested and want to
learn more.

Raising a fund is hard. You need a good team. We're missing a solid CFO who
has experience in the fund and accredited investor world. This person will
be in charge of deal mechanics, cash flow, capital calls, reporting, tax,
compliance, etc. It's not a job yet, but if we raise the money it will be.
Must be a US citizen or resident who is familiar with US hedge funds and
HNW investors. If you can recommend anyone, please do.

I'm happy to send our deck to anyone who may be interested.

Thank you,

